    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1986-12-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1986-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="171"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d171">
                <head>171. Memorandum From the President’s Acting Assistant for National Security
                    Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_KAGA_1">Keel</persName>) to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_RRW_1">Reagan</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d171fn1">Source: National Security Council,
                        National Security Council Institutional Files, Box SR–094, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> 252. Secret. Prepared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_DJ_1">Douglass</persName>. Copies were sent to <persName
                            corresp="#p_BGHW_1">Bush</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_RDT_1"
                            >Regan</persName>. <persName corresp="#p_PR_1">Pearson</persName>
                        initialed the memorandum on <persName corresp="#p_KAGA_1">Keel</persName>’s
                        behalf. The document notes that the meeting was scheduled for December 16
                        from 9:45 a.m. until 10:45 a.m. in the Cabinet Room. Attached at Tab B but
                        not printed is the meeting agenda. A stamped notation indicates <persName
                            corresp="#p_RRW_1">Reagan</persName> saw the memorandum on December 16.
                            <persName corresp="#p_RRW_1">Reagan</persName> wrote his initials in the
                        top right-hand corner of the memorandum.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1986-12-15">December 15, 1986</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="italic">MEETING WITH THE NATIONAL SECURITY COUNCIL</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">
                    <hi rend="roman">I.</hi> PURPOSE</p>
                <p>To review final recommendations from the Air Force and the Department of Defense
                    on <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">ICBM</gloss> Modernization.</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">
                    <hi rend="roman">II.</hi> BACKGROUND</p>
                <p>Our plan is to announce your decision on a new basing mode for the Peacekeeper
                    missile and a proper development program for the small <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1"
                        >ICBM</gloss> on 19 December 1986. This meeting will provide you with <gloss
                        target="#t_DOD_1">DOD</gloss>’s final recommendations and a briefing from
                    the Air Force.</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">
                    <hi rend="roman">III.</hi> PARTICIPANTS</p>
                <p>List of participants is at Tab C.<note n="2" xml:id="d171fn2">Attached but not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">
                    <hi rend="roman">IV.</hi> PRESS PLAN</p>
                <p>None</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">
                    <hi rend="roman">V.</hi> SEQUENCE OF EVENTS</p>
                <p>I will introduce the subject, Secretary <persName corresp="#p_WCWC_1"
                        >Weinberger</persName> will present a short briefing and discuss his
                    recommendations. Your remarks (Tab A)<note n="3" xml:id="d171fn3">Attached but
                        not printed are talking points prepared in the National Security
                        Council.</note> would then follow. A short discussion will follow your
                    remarks. Your final decision will be included in a National Security Decision
                    Directive that will be prepared for your signature on December 17th.</p>
            </div>
